    • Constructor Detail

      • Search

        public Search(java.lang.String searchString)
        Creates a search object by parsing the searchString to populate the lists of Tags that describe the set of Tracks represented by the Search.
        Parameters:
        searchString - Specifies what combination of Tags that describes the set of Tracks this Search represents. Tags are separated by spaces. Negative Tags are preceded by a '-'. SubSearches are separated by ' or '.

      • Search

        public Search(java.util.ArrayList<Tag> tagsToIntersect,
              java.util.ArrayList<Tag> tagsToExclude,
              Search subSearch)
        Creates a search object 'backwards' by passing in lists of Tag objects. Used to reconstruct saved Search objects from how they are stored in the database.
        Parameters:
        tagsToIntersect - positive Tags
        tagsToExclude - negative Tags
        subSearch - next Search in the linked list of sub Searches

    • Method Detail

      • executeSearch

        public java.util.ArrayList<Track> executeSearch()
        Creates the intersection of all of the TrackLists returned by getTracks for every Tag in tagsToIntersect. If tagsToIntersect is empty, finds the entire library. Merges all of the TrackLists returned by getTracks for every Tag in tagsToExclude Then finds the difference of the intersected Tracks and excluded Tracks. Finally finds the union of this difference and executeSearch() of any subSearch;
        Returns:
        a TrackList containing every Track found in all of the tagsToIntersect and in none of the tagsToExclude, as well as any returned by executing the subSearch;
